{
  "texts": [
    "Researchers often face difficulty locating the data they need, devoting up to 50-80% of their time to these obstacles (Eckert et al., 2020).",
    "Vangay et al. (2021) sustained identifying and addressing the root causes of annotation errors in public databases is essential for maintaining data integrity and ensuring the accuracy of downstream analyses and research applications.",
    "By taking into consideration of the factors that contribute to miss-annotations, efforts can be directed toward implementing quality control measures, improving metadata validation processes, enhancing contamination detection methods, and refining computational tools to minimize errors and improve the reliability of public databases.",
    "The availability of open-access metagenomic datasets provides a valuable resource for studying health-and disease-associated signatures of microbial communities.",
    "However, an ongoing debate within microbiome research revolves around addressing privacy concerns to protection of personal information (Guccione et al., 2023)."
  ]
}